---
title: Georgian Ajapsandali (v) with Aubergine, Pepper and Tomatoey Bulgur
description: Chef Lizzie finds cooking inspiration wherever she travels, and a recent trip to Georgia inspired her to recreate Ajapsandali, a traditional Georgian stew, for you to enjoy at home. Characteristically, Georgian stews use lots of garlic and fresh herbs, so it will be no surprise that this recipe is no different! Coriander, parsley and basil are combined in a rich veg-packed stew and served on top of nutty bulgar wheat to give the dish a really lovely texture.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/georgian-ajapsandali-04f85495-97fa4eea.jpg
